%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20entirely%20on%20my%20own%20when%20I%20was%2019.%20While%20I%20was%20enrolled%20in%20college%2C%20I%20worked%20full-time%20at%20night%20in%20the%20call%20center%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F49-most-promising-fintech-startups-according-top-vc-investors-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efintech%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jack%20Henry%20%26amp%3B%20Associates.%20It%20was%20a%20gritty%2C%20hands-on%20role%2C%20but%20an%20exciting%20time%20to%20be%20with%20the%20company%2C%20which%20was%20growing%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20a%20typical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-graduates-more-likely-have-friends-participate-community-civil-engagement-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20worked%20a%20lot%20so%20I%20could%20pay%20for%20my%20car%20and%20home.%20At%20work%2C%20I%20put%20my%20hand%20up%20any%20chance%20I%20could.%20I%20was%20never%20the%20smartest%20person%2C%20but%20I%20worked%20really%20hard%20and%20was%20always%20willing%20to%20figure%20out%20problems.%20Even%20if%20I'd%20never%20done%20something%2C%20I%20would%20figure%20it%20out.%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20fail%2C%20personally%20or%20professionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20served%20me%20well.%20I%20gained%20a%20reputation%20as%20someone%20who%20could%20execute%20tasks%20with%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20excellence%2C%20while%20also%20operating%20with%20empathy.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20left%20Jack%20Henry%20in%202022%2C%20after%2020%20years%2C%20I%20had%20become%20a%20vice%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252d83ace-5f10-4ebd-9d7f-bbfbc2271579%5C%22%3EMy%20husband%20handled%20childcare%20while%20I%20worked%20in%20NYC%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20I%20was%20a%20wife%2C%20mom%20of%20five%2C%20and%20had%20been%20a%20foster%20mother%20to%20seven%20children.%20I%20live%20in%20Missouri%2C%20but%20my%20reputation%20was%20so%20strong%20that%20the%20team%20at%20Fingercheck%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20HR%20platform%2C%20approached%20me%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-scale-up-small-business-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escaling%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20goal%20of%20acquisition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20traveling%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20spending%20two%20weeks%20in%20Brooklyn%20at%20a%20time%2C%20with%20a%20week%20at%20home%20in%20between.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwife-made-six-figures-husband-stayed-home-with-kids-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehusband%20handled%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20loading%20up%20the%20kids%20and%20bringing%20them%20to%20the%20school%20that%20they%20attended%2C%20where%20he%20was%20the%20superintendent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20three%20years%2C%20I%20helped%20scale%20Fingercheck.%20In%20October%202024%2C%20it%20was%20acquired%20for%20%24150%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222926%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiffany%20Haynes%20wearing%20a%20white%20zip-up%20sweater%20and%20standing%20in%20a%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945b4b5832e0ef1ead69a57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222195%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiffany%20Haynes%20wants%20her%20kids%20to%20know%20the%20value%20of%20hard%20work.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20credit%3A%20Teresa's%20PHOTOWORKS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207cd00d6-ecda-4bcd-8656-95d9b4a7fbc9%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20acquisition%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20founded%20a%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20at%20Fingercheck%20until%20this%20July%20to%20help%20with%20the%20transition.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20plan%20was%20to%20take%20time%20to%20reorient%20myself%20and%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20life%20had%20other%20plans.%20The%20school%20my%20husband%20led%20was%20affiliated%20with%20a%20local%20church.%20It%20grew%20so%20much%20that%20the%20church%20could%20no%20longer%20handle%20it%2C%20and%20this%20summer%2C%20we%20had%20a%20choice%20to%20make%3A%20let%20100%20kids%20find%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-microschool-pros-cons-personalized-learning-new-education-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20school%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20open%20our%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20whirlwind%20four%20months%2C%20but%20we%20did%20it.%20I%20call%20myself%20the%20quiet%20cofounder%20of%20the%20school%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20involved%20in%20day-to-day%20operations.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20doing%20some%20advising%20work%20and%20have%20a%20podcast%20called%20Between%20Builds.%20I'm%20also%20taking%20some%20time%20for%20myself%20to%20be%20whole%2C%20rather%20than%20hurried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223164%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiffany%20Haynes%20and%20her%20husband%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945b46504eda4732f2de825%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222373%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiffany%20Haynes%20and%20her%20husband%20connect%20every%20day%20over%20coffee.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20credit%3A%20Teresa's%20PHOTOWORKS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22183650f9-8e1d-426e-8b5a-e8c563bfe7f0%5C%22%3EWe%20connect%20almost%20daily%20over%20coffee%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20doesn't%20take%20a%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20his%20work%20is%20our%20way%20of%20giving%20back.%20When%20he%20left%20his%20paying%20job%2013%20years%20ago%20to%20enter%20education%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdone-being-girlboss-choosing-motherhood-over-money-and-career-growth-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%20the%20breadwinner%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We've%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20practice%20respecting%20one%20another's%20domains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20I%20