ing%20your%20morning%20Starbucks%20run.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20of%20the%20most%20fiscally%20savvy%20individuals%20are%20using%20tax%20rules%20and%20housing%20strategies%20to%20save%20big.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20to%20keep%20more%20of%20your%20money%20in%202026%2C%20the%20playbook%20goes%20well%20beyond%20cutting%20lattes%20or%20sticking%20to%20a%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20speaking%20to%20dozens%20of%20fiscally%20responsible%20individuals%20throughout%202025%20%E2%80%94%20from%20super%20savers%20to%20early%20retirees%20to%20financially%20independent%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20we%20rounded%20up%20the%20most%20creative%20advice%20we%20heard%20all%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20worked%20for%20them%2C%20it%20could%20work%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212394846-f924-41ae-9a40-5fd4de5530e5%5C%22%3E'Semi-retired'%20MDs%20leverage%20REPS%20to%20offset%20their%20clinical%20income%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kenji%20leti%20semi-retired%20MD%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694ed5c9832e0ef1ead6d839%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhysician%20couple%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20are%20the%20founders%20of%20Semi-Retired%20MD.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELetizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20started%20investing%20in%20real%20estate%20to%20supplement%2C%20and%20eventually%20fully%20replace%2C%20their%20incomes%20as%20doctors.%20Since%20buying%20their%20first%20investment%20property%20in%202015%2C%20they've%20expanded%20to%20more%20than%20100%20cash-flowing%20units%2C%20allowing%20them%20both%20to%20scale%20back%20in%20the%20hospital.%20They%20consider%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bsemi-retired%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20still%20work%20on%20their%20real%20estate%20portfolio%20and%20financial%20literary%20company%2C%20Semi-Retired%20MD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20scaled%20up%2C%20the%20couple%20discovered%20major%20tax%20benefits%20that%20come%20with%20owning%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20particular%20tax%20strategy%20enables%20them%20to%20shelter%20their%20physician%20income%20by%20using%20an%20IRS%20designation%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Breal%20estate%20professional%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20REPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20rental%20real%20estate%20losses%20are%20considered%20passive%20and%20can%20only%20offset%20passive%20income.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20working%20as%20an%20accountant%20and%20invest%20in%20real%20estate%20on%20the%20side%2C%20then%20the%20losses%20from%20your%20real%20estate%20business%20offset%20your%20rental%20income%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20can't%20take%20that%20loss%20and%20offset%20your%20accountant%20income.%20That's%20because%20they're%20two%20unrelated%20activities.%20However%2C%20if%20you're%20considered%20a%20real%20estate%20professional%2C%20it%20all%20becomes%20one%20big%20activity%2C%20and%20you%20can%20deduct%20rental%20losses%20against%20active%20forms%20of%20income%2C%20including%20W-2%20and%201099%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20savings%20can%20be%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20you%20earn%20%24250%2C000%20as%20an%20accountant%2C%20and%20you%20and%20your%20spouse%20run%20a%20rental%20real%20estate%20business%20that%20generates%20%24150%2C000%20in%20losses.%20If%20neither%20of%20you%20qualifies%20for%20REPS%2C%20you're%20taxed%20on%20all%20%24250%2C000.%20However%2C%20if%20one%20spouse%20claims%20REPS%2C%20you%20can%20deduct%20%24150%2C000%20from%20your%20%24250%2C0000%20income%2C%20meaning%20you'll%20only%20be%20taxed%20on%20%24100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20qualify%20for%20REPS%2C%20real%20estate%20must%20be%20your%20primary%20occupation%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20meet%20certain%20criteria%20each%20year%2C%20including%3A%20You%20have%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20750%20hours%20a%20year%20on%20real%20estate%20activities%2C%20more%20than%20half%20your%20working%20hours%20must%20be%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20materially%20participate%20in%20your%20rental%20activities%20by%20being%20involved%20with%20the%20day-to-day%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsakura%20transitioned%20to%20a%20part-time%20hospitalist%20in%202015%20so%20he%20could%20qualify%20for%20the%20status%2C%20and%20their%20rental%20losses%20could%20offset%20their%20income.%20Only%20one%20spouse%20needs%20to%20qualify%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20strategy%20is%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-strategies-for-marital-loophole-real-estate-investors-save-taxes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarital%20loophole%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22915fa500-a936-40a1-88b2-5a7c0edd239a%5C%22%3EOne%20millennial%20super%20saver%20uses%20every%20trick%20in%20the%20book%20to%20keep%20his%20costs%20low%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22866%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22carmelo%20camilleri%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694ed78904eda4732f2e268d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarmelo%20Camilleri%20and%20his%20father%2C%20Charlie.%3Cp%3ELeah%20Diel%20Photography%2FLeah%20Diel%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Carmelo%20Camilleri%20earned%20about%20%247%2C000%20working%20as%20a%20sales%20rep%20the%20summer%20after%20his%20freshman%20year%20of%20college%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20thing%20my%20father%20said%20to%20me%20was%2C%20'Don't%20spend%20it.%20Put%20it%20away%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20dad's%20advice%20stuck%2C%20and%20he%20maintained%20disciplined%20savings%20habits%20even%20as%20his%20income%20grew%20throughout%20and%20after%20college.%20He%20avoided%20paying%20for%20housing%20for%20years%20by%20living%20with%20his%20parents%20and%20used%20the%20savings%20to%20buy%20his%20first%20home%20at%20the%20age%20of%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECamilleri%20refuses%20to%20pay%20for%20subscriptions%2C%20which%20he%20considers%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20scam%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20won't%20pay%20top%20dollar%20for%20gas%20and%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20not%20the%20cheapest%20gas%20in%20the%20area%2C%20I'm%20not%20getting%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Camilleri%2C%20who%20price%20compares%20using%20the%20GasBuddy%20app.%20As%20for%20groceries%2C%20ShopRite%20tends%20to%20be%20the%20cheapest%20option%20in%20his%20area%2C%20but%20if%20they%20raise%20the%20prices%20on%20one%20of%20his%20staples%2C%20like%20ground%20turkey%2C%20he'll%20shop%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20how%20I%20live%20my%20life.%20I%20get%20the%20best%20deals%20on%20everything%2C%20and%20I%20never%20buy%20at%20the%20first%20price.%20I'm%20always%20trying%20to%20negotiate.%20I'm%20always%20looking%20to%20get%20the%20best%20price%20I%20possibly%20could%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20saved%20big%20on%20his%20home%20purchase%20by%20negotiating%20with%20the%20buyer.%20He%20landed%20on%20a%20price%20that%20was%20%2425%2C000%20lower%20than%20the%20seller's%20original%20asking%20price%2C%20partly%20due%20to%20his%20experience%20and%20partly%20due%20to%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20literally%20negotiating%20over%20the%20phone%20and%20making%20sales%20all%20day%20long.%20It's%20what%20I%20do%20for%20a%20living.%20I%20understand%20how%20negotiations%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20knew%20they%20weren't%20going%20to%20accept%20my%20first%20offer%2C%20but%20I%20started%20about%20%2450%2C000%20under%20asking%2C%20then%20they%20came%20back%20with%20a%20little%20bit%20higher%20than%20I%20wound%20up%20paying%2C%20and%20then%20we%20found%20some%20middle%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20lowballing%20wouldn't%20work%20in%20every%20situation.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20depends%20on%20the%20demand%20for%20that%20home.%20If%20there%20were%2010%20people%20bidding%20on%20the%20home%2C%20I'm%20sure%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20worked%20out%20in%20my%20favor.%20In%20this%20instance%2C%20I%20do%20actually%20feel%20like%20I%20might%20have%20gotten%20lucky%20because%20it%20is%20a%20beautiful%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e3feae60-0f99-4d81-8f5b-9bcc577c13b7%5C%22%3EOne%20couple%20turns%20their%20primary%20home%20into%20an%20income-producing%20asset%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222195%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jeff%20white%20suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694ed85804eda4732f2e269c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhite%20and%20Bola%C3%B1os%20take%20one%20trip%20a%20month%20in%20early%20retirement.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jeff%20White%20and%20Suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20retirees%20Jeff%20and%20Suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%20have%20a%20wealth-building%20system%20on%20lock.%20It%20requires%20moving%20homes%20once%20a%20year%20and%20sometimes%20living%20with%20roommates%2C%20but%20it's%20saved%20them%20enough%20money%20to%20grow%20a%20sizable%20real%20estate%20portfolio%20and%20walk%20away%20from%20their%20day%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20strategy%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20involves%20renting%20out%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20primary%20residence%20to%20offset%20or%20eliminate%20their%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20they%20move%20once%20a%20year%20is%20that%20they%20want%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20owner-occupied%20financing%2C%20which%20typically%20comes%20with%20more%20favorable%20terms%2C%20such%20as%20a%20lower%20down%20payment%20and%20interest%20rate%2C%20compared%20to%20financing%20for%20investment%20properties.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20one%20stipulation%20with%20this%20type%20of%20financing%20is%20that%20you%20have%20to%20live%20in%20the%20property%20for%20at%20least%2012%20months.%20After%20the%20year%20is%20up%2C%20they%20convert%20the%20property%20they%20were%20living%20in%20into%20a%20true%20investment%20property%2C%20buy%20and%20move%20into%20the%20next%20place%2C%20and%20repeat%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Denver-based%20couple%20began%20house-hacking%2C%20they%20lived%20comfortably%20in%20a%20%241%2C500-per-month%20condo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20single%20paragraph%20from%20a%20book%20called%20%26quot%3BBuild%20a%20Rental%20Property%20Empire%26quot%3B%20initiated%20their%20lifestyle%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20it%20said%20was%3A%20'Buy%20a%20two-%20to%20four-unit%20property%2C%20live%20in%20one%20unit%2C%20rent%20out%20the%20others.%20You%20could%20take%20your%20housing%20down%20to%20zero%20and%20live%20for%20free%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20White.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Hey%2C%20we're%20paying%20%241%2C500%20to%20live%20at%20this%20beautiful%20condo%20with%20a%20spiral%20staircase%20and%20a%20duck%20pond%2C%20high%20ceilings%2C%20and%20big%20windows.%20It's%20amazing.%20But%20what%20if%20we%20took%20it%20down%20to%20%240%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20done%20one%20house%20hack%20a%20year%20for%20the%20last%20eight%20years%2C%20and%20their%20cash%20flow%20has%20grown%20with%20each%20addition%20to%20their%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20ran%20the%20math%2C%20and%20Suleyka%20and%20I%20would%20still%20be%20working%20if%20we%20stopped%20after%20that%20first%20house%20and%20just%20gave%20up%20and%20went%20back%20to%20a%20condo.%20We%20would%20both%20still%20be%20working%20probably%20for%20another%2030%20years%2C%2040%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20White.%20%26quot%3BThis%20expedited%20our%20financial%20independence%20journey.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuper-savers-early-retirement-best-money-saving